        <td style="width:315px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Cross-Over</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> or is the point where the acceleration changes sign </text><image src="Red-14-1b.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;"/></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Cross-over Jerk</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> is the rate of change of acceleration (Jerk) at &apos;cross-over&apos;. It is important because this is where backlash is traversed. A </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">low jerk</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> means the acceleration is not changing rapidly. When the acceleration is not changing rapidly and the absolute acceleration is also near to zero, then the velocity is not changing rapidly. Thus the so-called backlash after impact also tends to be lower.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
